My double cleansing routine ft. @anua.skincare Heartleaf Cleansing Oil and Cleansing Foam ☘️🤍

I recently tried Anua’s cleansing oil and cleansing foam, and as someone with dry, sensitive skin, I was pleasantly surprised. The cleansing oil, enriched with natural oils like olive and jojoba, effortlessly dissolved my makeup and daily grime without leaving any greasy residue. It left my skin feeling nourished and soft, which is a big plus for me.

Following up with the cleansing foam was a delight. It lathered up into a gentle, airy foam that effectively cleansed my skin without stripping it of moisture. After using both, my skin felt refreshed and clean, without any tightness or irritation. I appreciate that both products are formulated with natural ingredients, which my sensitive skin appreciates.

Thank you @maccaron_beauty @anua.skincare 🤍

How to create the duplicate mirror effect in capcut under 30 second?

1.  Select the clip and duplicate it.
2.  Convert the duplicate to an overlay and position it under the main clip.
3.  Use the “Transform” tool to flip the overlay clip using the “Rotate” option.
4.  Apply a mask, selecting “Horizontal” and rotating it 90 degrees.
5.  Adjust the clip’s positioning and timing as needed.
6. To refine it, go back to the mask option, select “Feather”, and adjust the feathering to your liking.

This effect is super easy to create, just follow these simple steps and level up your editing/content creation game ✨
